values:
I actually lost pretty much all excitment for going back to purchase.&nbsp;

New smoking rules can suck my ass. I would rather be ticketed than follow some gay policy.

A lot of good, interesting fun people are gone.&nbsp;

And, the stood is closed until mid semester.&nbsp;

The library is fucked and that whole area is closed.&nbsp;

No thanks, I think I would rather fight with my mother all day right now.

I love Vin Diesel. Why? Because he has a sexy voice. And because he has a sense of humor. Also, he is obviously not a dumb guy.&nbsp;That and I like just about anyone who can kick down a door. Him and Alan Rickman should have a voice off. I bet if either of them read aloud instructions about how to build a computer, or any book by Dickens, equal dryness, every woman, some men, would be very happy people.

I have become obsessed with watchng G.I. Jane. I can't explain it past my feminist upbrining and need to see a woman kick some fucking butt at a mans game.&nbsp;That and Viggo Mortenson makes me ( a crazy blue stater) actually like a millitary man and a southern man, all in one! He is just banging, even with the bum knee. Though I have to say, not a big fan or non-rhyming poety, call me immature, but I get it, it was meaninful. Oh and he just keeps wearing those short shorts. I love short shorts on guys. Hot. Hot hot hot.&nbsp;

Speaking of, today on the train there was this dick head ass hole douche, I say this because he was the typical 23-year-old attractive white male, thin sporty, nice long hair stating he was cool, hip, not corporate. With movie star sun glasses and three days worth of stubble he knew every&nbsp; female 15-30 was looking his way. Not to mention he must have been wearing his girlfriend's short shorts (if he bought them himself (black with yellow and orange stripes on the side) he would loose major cool points) anyway this arse stutted out of the train to his stop. I think I am most mad because I could tell he was a prick and still couldn't stop staring.

Hm, well, today, for the third time in about a month and a half's time, the store I work at got broken into again.

Usually it takes three hours from normal opening time until the cops leave and the store is opened to the public.&nbsp;

During these three hours we are not paid, our attendence is not marked and we are told to either wait infront of the store or go do something and come back.

After three hours I left. The twenty five bucks I would have made today given the rest of my time left by the time they opened wasn't worth waiting around in the fucking heat, nor was hanging out in my mothers office very fun as she was freaking out.&nbsp;

Went home, went to sleep. What a stupid day, why did I wake up?

Last night at about two in the morning I decided drinking a glass full of vodka to "calm" down and sleep was a good idea. I woke up in a different outfit than the on I had put on, and the bed was soaking wet as I had drunkenly sleep walked to get water and spilled it every where. Fantastic. At least this is what I assume happened. There was a glass I hadn't remembered bringing in.&nbsp;

Also, still very very drunk when I got to work. Quite the adventure.

And to make the day better as I am leaving the boss man informs me I am working tomorrow. Even though I had made plans with my family. Guess not.&nbsp;

Results of the back doctor: I learned today that the back surgeon specialist dood&nbsp;I see, also dabbles in acupuncture. I personally avoid homeopathic and off the chart medicines, but if this guy who went through more schooling than years I have been alive thinks there is merit I'll give it a go. Today I had a pin in the back of my neck for about twenty minutes. It hurt a bit, but oddly enough, all fucking day that spot hasn't hurt. I have to go back every week for the stuff. Also, I was put on some anti-seiziure medication, the new pancea. Perhaps it will doubley work to level moods as well as eliminate pain. I am doubtful. But maybe just maybe. Funny, I could have been put on this stuff by a therapist and my parents would be outraged, but by a back docotor, sure why not.&nbsp;

By the by, I am in a wonderful mood though its hard to tell.

Got my bangs trimmed very short by a very pretty asian lady today, she had black and blue hair and was skinnier than I ever was when I was a lass.&nbsp;

Maybe, I could switch to the new meds and go off the pill,, if&nbsp;it does the same mood&nbsp;effects,&nbsp;and I could loose the stupid weight it made me gain. (yes it was only like ten/fifteen pounds, and its a vanity issue, but I am allowed to be vain.)

And in other news, my hair looks like a wig, it is a bit of a magenta but more pink color. Actually its really just a bright deep pink. I wanted red, but pink is still awesome.&nbsp;

Might have work tomorrow, don't know, my mother likes to tell my bosses things without telling me and forgets to tell me things until she has had half a bottle of wine. So, we'll see.
